This function `mask_pii` takes a string `text` and applies a series of regular expression substitutions to mask potential personally identifiable information (PII) such as emails, US phone numbers, social security numbers (SSNs), and 16-digit credit card numbers. Each type of PII is replaced with a stable placeholder, ensuring that the context of the text remains intact while sensitive information is redacted.
